quotecontent">The MMC3 has 4 pairs of registers at $8000-$9FFF, $A000-$BFFF, $C000-$DFFF, and $E000-$FFFF - even addresses ($8000, $8002, etc.) select the low register and odd addresses ($8001, $8003, etc.) select the high register in each pair.</div><br />I don't understand what it means by "in each pair".<br /><br />So, in addition to setting the header correctly, one must set things at the address in the mapper correctly too, in order for a game to run?<br /><br />Also, it says:<br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">Mirroring ($A000-$BFFE, even)</div>
